  <statement>
      <p>
          An engineer wants to know the probability that a new anti-rust coat stays on when exposed to rain-like conditions.  She wants to find a <m> 99</m>% confidence interval with margin of error <m>ME=0.03</m>.
      </p>
      <p>
          A previous study showed that  of <m>46\ </m> tested samples exposed to rain-like conditions,  <m>25\ </m>had the coating stay on.  How many samples should she now test to obtain a <m>99</m>% confidence interval with margin of error <m>ME=0.03</m>?
      </p>
      
